<TITLE> HC allows MFs to issue rights shares </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 8 (bdnews24.com)The High Court on Sunday gave the green light for mutual funds to issue rights shares or bonus shares, overturning an amendment by the Securities and Exchange Commission barring them from doing so. A High Court bench of Justice Syed Mahmud Hossain and Justice Quamrul Islam Siddiqui gave the verdict on a petition against the regulator's decision. The verdict, however, said that the ruling would be applicable only on mutual funds that were listed when the amendment was made by the SEC, said M Zahir, counsel for the petitioners. bd
